obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34242)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34242&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi School Education`
  line `Act, 1973.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Administrator may, by notification, appoint and`
  line `different dates ^1 may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference to the`
  line `commencement of this Act in relation to any provision thereof shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `date on which that provision comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 28th April, 1973, vide notification of the Delhi Administration in the Education Deptt. No. F. 5/15/72-Education`
  line `dated 28th April, 1973, in respect of the provisions except Chapters II to V (both inclusive), sections 16, 17, 18, 22 and 27).`
  line
  line `31st December, 1973, vide notification No. F. 5/15/72-Education (i), dated 31st December, 1973, Delhi Gazette, Extraordinary,`
  line `Pt. IV, dated 31st December, 1973, in respect of Chapters II to V (both inclusive), sections, 16, 17, 18, 22 and 27,`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34243)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34243&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “Administrator” means the Administrator of the Union territory of Delhi appointed by the`
  line `President under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) “Advisory Board” means the Board referred to in section 22;`
  line
  line `(c) “aid” means any aid granted to a recognised school by the Central Government,`
  line `Administrator, a local authority or any other authority designated by the Central Government,`
  line `Administrator or a local authority;`
  line
  line `(d) “aided school” means a recognised private school which is receiving aid in the form of`
  line `maintenance grant from the Central Government, Administrator or a local authority or any other`
  line `authority designated by the Central Government, Administrator or a local authority;`
  line
  line `(e) “appropriate authority” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a school recognised or to be recognised by an authority designated or`
  line `sponsored by the Central Government, that authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a school recognised or to be recognised by the Delhi Administration, the`
  line `Administrator or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a school recognised or to be recognised by the Municipal Corporation of`
  line `Delhi, that Corporation;`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of any other school, the Administrator or any other officer authorised by him`
  line `in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(f) “Delhi” means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(g) “Director” means the Director of Education, Delhi, and includes any other officer authorised`
  line `by him to perform all or any of the functions of the Director under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) “employee” means a teacher and includes every other employee working in a recognised`
  line school;
  line
  line `(i) “existing employee” means an employee of an existing school who is employed in such school`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, and includes an employee who was employed in`
  line `such school for a period of not less than twelve months immediately preceding the 2nd day of`
  line `September, 1972;`
  line
  line `(j) “existing school” means a recognised private school which is in existence at the`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) “Head of school” means the principal academic officer, by whatever name called, of a`
  line `recognised school;`
  line
  line `(l) “local authority” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an area within the local limits of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi, that`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to an area within the local limits of the New Delhi Municipal Committee, that`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to an area within the local limits of the Delhi Cantonment Board, that Board;`
  line
  line `(m) “manager”, in relation to a school, means the person, by whatever name called, who is`
  line `entrusted, either on the date on which this Act comes into force or, as the case may be, under a`
  line `scheme of management made under section 5, with the management of the affairs of that school;`
  line
  line `(n) “managing committee” means the body of individuals who are entrusted with the management`
  line `of any recognised private school;`
  line
  line `(o) “minority school” means a school established and administered by a minority having the right`
  line `to do so under clause (1) of article 30 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(p) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(q) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) “private school” means a school which is not run by the Central Government, Administrator, a`
  line `local authority or any other authority designated or sponsored by the Central Government,`
  line `Administrator or a local authority;`
  line
  line `(s) “public examination” means an examination conducted by the Central Board of Secondary`
  line `Education, Council for Indian School Certificate Examinations or any other Board which may`
  line `hereafter be established for the purpose, and recognised by the Administrator or any other officer`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(t) “recognised school” means a school recognised by the appropriate authority;`
  line
  line `(u) “school” includes a pre-primary, primary, middle and higher secondary school, and also`
  line `includes any other institution which imparts education or training below the degree level, but does not`
  line `include an institution which imparts technical education;`
  line
  line `(v) “school property” means all movable and immovable property belonging to, or in the`
  line `possession of, the school and all other rights and interests in, or arising out of, such property, and`
  line `includes land, building and its appurtenances, playgrounds, hostels, furniture, books, apparatus, maps,`
  line `equipment, utensils, cash, reserve funds investments and bank balances;`
  line
  line `(w) “teacher” includes the Head of a school;`
  line
  line `(x) “unaided minority school” means a recognised minority school which does not receive any`
  line aid.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34244)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Administrator to regulate education in schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34244&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may regulate`
  line `education in all the schools in Delhi in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may establish and maintain any school in Delhi or may permit any person or`
  line `local authority to establish and maintain any school in Delhi, subject to compliance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the commencement of this Act and subject to the provisions of clause (1) of article`
  line `30 of the Constitution, the establishment of a new school or the opening of a higher class or the closing`
  line `down of an existing class in any existing school in Delhi shall be subject to the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder and any school or higher class established or opened otherwise than in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act shall not be recognised by the appropriate authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34245)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Recognition of schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34245&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate authority may, on an application made to it in the`
  line `prescribed form and in the prescribed manner, recognise any private school:`
  line
  line `Provided that no school shall be recognised unless—`
  line
  line `(a) it has adequate funds to ensure its financial stability and regular payment of salary and`
  line `allowances to its employees;`
  line
  line `(b) it has a duly approved scheme of management as required by section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) it has suitable or adequate accommodation and sanitary facilities having regard, among other`
  line `factors, to the number, age and sex of the pupils attending it;`
  line
  line `(d) it provides for approved courses of study and efficient instruction;`
  line
  line `(e) it has teachers with prescribed qualifications; and`
  line
  line `(f) it has the prescribed facilities for physical education, library service, laboratory work,`
  line `workshop practice or co-curricular activities.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for recognition of a school shall be entertained and considered by the`
  line `appropriate authority and the decision thereon shall be communicated to the applicant within a period of`
  line `four months from the date of the receipt of the application; and where recognition is not granted, the`
  line `reasons for not granting such recognition shall also be communicated to the applicant within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(3) Where recognition to a school is refused, any person aggrieved by such refusal may, within thirty`
  line `days from the date of communication to him, of such refusal, appeal against such refusal, in the`
  line `prescribed manner, to the prescribed authority and the decision of the prescribed authority thereon shall`
  line `be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the prescribed authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said period of thirty days, extend, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded by it in writing, the said period by a further period of sixty days.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the managing committee of a school obtains recognition by fraud, misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of material particulars, or where, after obtaining recognition, the school fails to continue to`
  line `comply with any of the conditions specified in the proviso to sub-section (1). the authority granting the`
  line `recognition may, after giving the managing committee of the school a reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against the proposed action, withdraw the recognition granted to such school under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) The recognition granted under sub-section (1) shall not, by itself, entitle any school to receive aid.`
  line
  line `(6) Every existing school shall be deemed to have been recognised under this section and shall be`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such school does not satisfy any of the conditions specified in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1), the prescribed authority may require the school to satisfy such conditions and such other`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, within a specified period and if any such condition is not satisfied,`
  line `recognition may be withdrawn from such school.`
  line
  line `(7) Every school, whose recognition is withdrawn under sub-section (4) or sub-section (6), may`
  line `appeal to the prescribed authority, who shall dispose of the appeal within six months from the date of`
  line `presentation of the appeal in such manner as may be prescribed, and if the appeal is not disposed of`
  line `within that period, the order for the withdrawal of recognition shall, on the expiry of the said period of six`
  line `months, stand cancelled.`
  line
  line `(8) On hearing an appeal preferred under sub-section (3) or sub-section (7), the prescribed authority`
  line `may, after giving the appellant a reasonable opportunity of being heard, confirm, modify or reverse the`
  line `order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34246)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Scheme of management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34246&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law, the managing committee of`
  line `every recognised school shall make, in accordance with the rules made under this Act and with the`
  line `previous approval of the appropriate authority, a scheme of management for such school:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a recognised private school which does not receive any aid, the scheme of`
  line `management shall apply with such variations and modifications as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that so much of this sub-section as relates to the previous approval of the appropriate`
  line `authority, shall not apply to a scheme of management for an unaided minority school.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme may be made, in like manner, to add to, vary or modify any scheme made under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34247)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Aid to recognised schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34247&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, pay to the`
  line `Administrator, for distribution of aid to recognised private schools, not being primary schools recognised`
  line `by a local authority, such sums of money as that Government may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that no existing school receiving, immediately before the commencement of this Act, aid`
  line `shall be eligible for the continuance of such aid unless it complies, within such period as may be specified`
  line `by the Director, with the conditions specified in the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority competent to grant the aid may stop, reduce or suspend aid for violation of any of`
  line `the conditions prescribed in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The aid may cover such part of the expenditure of the school as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) No payment, out of the aid given for salary, allowances and provident fund of employees of the`
  line `school, shall be made for any other purpose.`
  line
  line `(5) No aid shall be given to a school the management of which has been taken over under section 20.`
  line
  line `(6) No unrecognised school shall be eligible to receive any aid or any benefit made available to`
  line `private schools by the Administrator or any agency of the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34248)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `School property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34248&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The management of every aided school shall furnish to the appropriate`
  line `authority, initially, at the time of grant of aid and thereafter annually, a statement containing a list of`
  line `school property together with such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no transfer,`
  line `mortgage or lease of any movable or immovable property of an aided school, not being the property`
  line `specified in the rules, shall be made except with the previous permission of the appropriate authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the appropriate authority omits or fails to dispose of the application for such`
  line `permission within sixty days from the date of receipt of the application in this behalf, the permission`
  line `shall, on the expiry of the said period of sixty days, be deemed to have been granted.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by the grant or refusal of permission under sub-section (2) may prefer, in`
  line `such form and within such time as may be prescribed, appeal to the Administrator against such grant or`
  line `refusal of permission and the decision of the Administrator thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Any transaction made in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (2), or, as the case may be,`
  line `decision of the Administrator, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34249)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Terms and conditions of service of employees of recognised private schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34249&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Administrator may make rules regulating the minimum qualifications for recruitment, and the conditions`
  line `of service, of employees of recognised private schools:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary nor the rights in respect of leave of absence, age of retirement and`
  line `pension of an employee in the employment of an existing school at the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `be varied to the disadvantage of such employee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such employee shall be entitled to opt for terms and conditions of service`
  line `as they were applicable to him immediately before the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rule that may be made in this behalf, no employee of a recognised private school`
  line `shall be dismissed, removed or reduced in rank nor shall his service be otherwise terminated except with`
  line `the prior approval of the Director.`
  line
  line `(3) Any employee of a recognised private school who is dismissed, removed or reduced in rank may,`
  line `within three months from the date of communication to him of the order of such dismissal, removal or`
  line `reduction in rank, appeal against such order to the Tribunal constituted under section 11.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the managing committee of a recognised private school intends to suspend any of its`
  line `employees, such intention shall be communicated to the Director and no such suspension shall be made`
  line `except with the prior approval of the Director:`
  line
  line `Provided that the managing committee may suspend an employee with immediate effect and without`
  line `the prior approval of the Director if it is satisfied that such immediate suspension is necessary by reason`
  line `of the gross misconduct, within the meaning of the Code of Conduct prescribed under section 9, of the`
  line `employee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such immediate suspension shall remain in force for more than a period of`
  line `fifteen days from the date of suspension unless it has been communicated to the Director and approved by`
  line `him before the expiry of the said period.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the intention to suspend, or the immediate suspension of, an employee is communicated to`
  line `the Director, he may, if he is satisfied that there are adequate and reasonable grounds for such suspension,`
  line `accord his approval to such suspension.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34250)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Employees to be governed by a Code of Conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34250&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every employee of a recognised school shall`
  line `be governed by such Code of Conduct as may be prescribed and on the violation of any provision of such`
  line `Code of Conduct, the employee shall be liable to such disciplinary action as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34270)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Salaries of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34270&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The scales of pay and allowances, medical facilities, pension,`
  line `gratuity, provident fund and other prescribed benefits of the employees of a recognised private school`
  line `shall not be less than those of the employees of the corresponding status in schools run by the appropriate`
  line `authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the scales of pay and allowances, medical facilities, pension, gratuity, provident`
  line `fund and other prescribed benefits of the employees of any recognised private school are less than those`
  line `of the employees of the corresponding status in the schools run by the appropriate authority, the`
  line `appropriate authority shall direct, in writing, the managing committee of such school to bring the same up`
  line `to the level of those of the employees of the corresponding status in schools run by the appropriate`
  line `authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the failure to comply with such direction shall be deemed to be non-compliance`
  line `with the conditions for continuing recognition of an existing school and the provisions of section 4 shall`
  line `apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) The managing committee of every aided school shall deposit, every month, its share towards pay`
  line `and allowances, medical facilities, pension, gratuity, provident fund and other prescribed benefits with the`
  line `Administrator and the Administrator shall disburse, or cause to be disbursed, within the first week of`
  line `every month, the salaries and allowances to the employees of the aided schools.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34271)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Tribunal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34271&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator shall, by notification, constitute a Tribunal, to be known as the`
  line `"Delhi School Tribunal", consisting of one person:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be so appointed unless he has held office as a District Judge or any`
  line `equivalent judicial office.`
  line
  line `(2) If any vacancy, other than a temporary absence, occurs in the office of the presiding officer of the`
  line `Tribunal, the Administrator shall appoint another person, in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section, to fill the vacancy and the proceedings may be continued before the Tribunal from the stage at`
  line `which the vacancy is filled.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administrator shall make available to the Tribunal such staff as may be necessary in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred in connection with the Tribunal shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of the`
  line `discharge of its functions including the place or places at which it shall hold its sittings.`
  line
  line `(6) The Tribunal shall for the purpose of disposal of an appeal preferred under this Act have the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a court of appeal by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and shall also`
  line `have the power to stay the operation of the order appealed against on such terms as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34252)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Chapter not to apply to unaided minority school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34252&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Chapter shall`
  line `apply to an unaided minority school.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34253)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to prescribe minimum qualifications for recruitment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34253&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may make`
  line `rules regulating the minimum qualifications for, and method of, recruitment of employees of unaided`
  line `minority schools:`
  line
  line `Provided that no qualification shall be varied to the disadvantage of an existing employee of an`
  line `unaided minority school.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34254)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to prescribe Code of Conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34254&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every employee of an unaided minority school shall be`
  line `governed by such Code of Conduct as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34255)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Contract of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34255&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The managing committee of every unaided minority school shall enter`
  line `into a written contract of service with every employee of such school:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, at the commencement of this Act, there is no written contract of service in relation to`
  line `any existing employee of an unaided minority school, the managing committee of such school shall enter`
  line `into such contract within a period of three months from such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no contract referred to in the foregoing proviso shall vary to the disadvantage of`
  line `any existing employee the term of any contract subsisting at the commencement of this Act between him`
  line `and the school.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every contract of service referred to in sub-section (1) shall be forwarded by the`
  line `managing committee of the concerned unaided minority school to the Administrator who shall, on receipt`
  line `of such copy, register it in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every contract of service referred to in sub-section (1) shall provide for the following matters,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service of the employee, including the scale of pay and other`
  line `allowances to which he shall be entitled;`
  line
  line `(b) the leave of absence, age of retirement, pension and gratuity, or, contributory provident fund`
  line `in lieu of pension and gratuity, and medical and other benefits to which the employee shall be`
  line entitled;
  line
  line `(c) the penalties which may be imposed on the employee for the violation of any Code of`
  line `Conduct or the breach of any term of the contract entered into by him;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which disciplinary proceedings in relation to the employee shall be conducted`
  line `and the procedure which shall be followed before any employee is dismissed, removed from service`
  line `or reduced in rank;`
  line
  line `(e) arbitration of any dispute arising out of any breach of contract between the employee and the`
  line `managing committee with regard to—`
  line
  line `(i) the scales of pay and other allowances,`
  line
  line `(ii) leave of absence, age of retirement, pension, gratuity, provident fund, medical and other`
  line benefits,
  line
  line `(iii) any disciplinary action leading to the dismissal or removal from service or reduction in`
  line `rank of the employee;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which, in the opinion of the managing committee, ought to be, or may be,`
  line `specified in such contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34256)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Admission to recognised schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34256&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A child who has not attained the age of five years, shall`
  line `not be admitted to class I, or an equivalent class or any class higher than class I, in a recognised school.`
  line
  line `(2) A student seeking admission for the first time in a recognised school in a class higher than class I`
  line `shall not be admitted to that class if his age reduced by the number of years of normal school study`
  line `between that class and class I or an equivalent class, falls short of five years.`
  line
  line `(3) Admission to a recognised school or to any class thereof shall be regulated by rules made in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34257)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Fees and other charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34257&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No aided school shall levy any fee or collect any other charge or`
  line `receive any other payment except those specified by the Director.`
  line
  line `(2) Every aided school having different rates of fees or other charges or different funds shall obtain`
  line `prior approval of the prescribed authority before levying such fees or collecting such charges or creating`
  line `such funds.`
  line
  line `(3) The manager of every recognised school shall, before the commencement of each academic`
  line `session, file with the Director a full statement of the fees to be levied by such school during the ensuing`
  line `academic session, and except with the prior approval of the Director, no such school shall charge, during`
  line `that academic session, any fee in excess of the fee specified by its manager in the said statement.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34258)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `School Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34258&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every aided school, there shall be a fund, to be called the "School Fund",`
  line `and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) any aid granted by the Administrator,`
  line
  line `(b) income accruing to the school by way of fees, charges or other payments, and`
  line
  line `(c) any other contributions, endowments and the like.`
  line
  line `(2) The School Fund and all other funds, including the Pupils' Fund, established with the approval of`
  line `the Administrator, shall be accounted for and operated in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) In every recognised unaided school, there shall be a fund, to be called the "Recognised Unaided`
  line `School Fund", and there shall be credited thereto income accruing to the school by way of—`
  line
  line `(a) fees,`
  line
  line `(b) any charges and payments which may be realised by the school for other specific purposes,`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) any other contributions, endowments, gifts and the like,`
  line
  line `(4) (a) Income derived by unaided schools by way of fees shall be utilised only for such educational`
  line `purposes as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) charges and payments realised and all other contributions, endowments and gifts received by the`
  line `school shall be utilised only for the specific purpose for which they were realised or received.`
  line
  line `(5) The managing committee of every recognised private school shall file every year with the`
  line `Director such duly audited financial and other returns as may be prescribed, and every such return shall`
  line `be audited by such authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34259)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Affiliations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34259&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of any public examination every recognised higher secondary`
  line `school shall be affiliated to one or more of the Boards or Council conducting such examination and shall`
  line `fulfil the conditions specified by the Board or Council in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The students of recognised higher secondary schools shall be prepared for, and presented to, the`
  line `public examinations or such other form of evaluation held or made for the students of such schools.`
  line
  line `(3) The students of every recognised middle school shall be prepared for, and presented to, such`
  line `public examination as may be held by the Directorate of Education, Delhi, for the students of such`
  line schools.
  line
  line `(4) Every student of a recognised primary school shall be prepared for, and presented to, the public`
  line `examination held by a local authority competent to hold such examination for the students of such`
  line schools.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34260)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Taking over the management of schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34260&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the Administrator is satisfied that the`
  line `managing committee or manager of any school, whether recognised or not, has neglected to perform any`
  line `of the duties imposed on it by or under this Act or any rule made thereunder and that it is expedient in the`
  line `interests of school education to take over the management of such school, he may, after giving the`
  line `managing committee or the manager of such school, a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against`
  line `the proposed action, take over the management of such school for a limited period not exceeding three`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the management of a school has been taken over for a period of three years or`
  line `less, the Administrator may, if he is of opinion that in order to secure proper management of the school it`
  line `is expedient that such management should continue to be in force after the expiry of the said limited`
  line `period, he may, from time to time, issue directions for the continuance of such management for such`
  line `period not exceeding one year at a time as he may think fit, so, however, that the total period for which`
  line `such management is taken over shall not, in any case, exceed five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the management of any school is taken over under sub-section (1), every person in`
  line `charge of the management of such school immediately before its management is taken over, shall deliver`
  line `possession of the school property to the Administrator or any officer authorised by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) After taking over the management of any school under this section, the Administrator may arrange`
  line `to manage the school through the Director or any other person authorised by the Director in this behalf`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the "authorised officer").`
  line
  line `(4) Where the management of any school has been taken over under sub-section (1), the managing`
  line `committee or manager of such school may, within three months from the date of taking over, appeal to`
  line `the Administrator, who may after considering the representation made by the managing committee or the`
  line `manager, pass such orders, including an order for the restoration of the management or for the reduction`
  line `of the period during which the management of such school shall remain vested in the Administrator, as he`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the management of a school has been taken over under this section, the Administrator shall`
  line `pay such rent as may be payable for the building of the school to the person entitled to receive it as was`
  line `being paid by the managing committee or the manager immediately before the management of such`
  line `school was taken over.`
  line
  line `(6) During such period as any school remains under the management of the authorised officer—`
  line
  line `(a) the service conditions, as approved by the Administrator, of the employees of the school who`
  line `were in employment immediately before the date on which the management was taken over, shall not`
  line `be varied to their disadvantage;`
  line
  line `(b) all educational facilities which the school had been affording immediately before such`
  line `management was taken over, shall continue to be afforded;`
  line
  line `(c) the School Fund, the Pupils Fund and the Management Fund and any other existing fund`
  line `shall continue to be available to the authorised officer for being spent for the purposes of the school;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) no resolution passed at any meeting of the managing committee of such school shall be given`
  line `effect to unless approved by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34261)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Section 20 not to apply to minority schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34261&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in section 20 shall apply to`
  line `any minority school.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34262)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Delhi Schools Education Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34262&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an Advisory Board for school`
  line `education, to be called the "Delhi School Education Advisory Board" for the purpose of advising the`
  line `Administrator on matters of policy relating to education in Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Board shall be constituted by the Administrator and shall consist of a Chairman and`
  line `fourteen other members, to be nominated by the Administrator.`
  line
  line `(3) The Advisory Board constituted under sub-section (2) shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) Heads of recognised private schools;`
  line
  line `(b) representatives of the organisations of teachers of the recognised private schools;`
  line
  line `(c) managers of the recognised private schools;`
  line
  line `(d) representatives of parents or guardians of students of recognised private schools; and`
  line
  line `(e) eminent educationists.`
  line
  line `(4) The Advisory Board shall regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) The terms of office of every member of the Board and travelling and other allowances payable to`
  line `a member of the Board shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34263)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34263&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may delegate all or any of his powers, duties and`
  line `functions under this Act to the Director or any other officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person to whom any power is delegated under sub-section (1), may exercise that power in`
  line `the same manner and with the same effect as if such power had been conferred on him directly by this Act`
  line `and not by way of delegation.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34264)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Inspection of schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34264&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every recognised school shall be inspected at least once in each`
  line `financial year in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director may also arrange special inspection of any school on such aspects of its working as`
  line `may, from time to time, be considered necessary by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director may give directions to the manager requiring the manager to rectify any defect or`
  line `deficiency found at the time of inspection or otherwise in the working of the school.`
  line
  line `(4) If the manager fails to comply with any direction given under sub-section (3), the Director may,`
  line `after considering the explanation or report, if any, given or made by the manager, take such action as he`
  line `may think fit, including—`
  line
  line `(a) stoppage of aid,`
  line
  line `(b) withdrawal of recognition, or`
  line
  line `(c) except in the case of a minority school, taking over of the school under section 20.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34265)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34265&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter in relation to which the Administrator or the Director or any other person authorised by the`
  line `Administrator or Director or any other officer or authority appointed or specified by or under this Act, is`
  line `empowered by or under this Act to exercise any power, and no injunction shall be granted by any civil`
  line `court in respect of anything which is done or intended to be done by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34266)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34266&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Administrator, Director or any other person authorised by the Administrator or Director for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34267)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Liability of manager to punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34267&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If the manager of any recognised private school.—`
  line
  line `(a) omits or fails, without any reasonable excuse, to carry out any orders made by the Tribunal, or`
  line
  line `(b) presents any student for any public examination without complying with the provisions of`
  line `section 19, or`
  line
  line `(c) omits or fails to deliver any school property to the Administrator or any officer authorised by`
  line `him under sub-section (2) of section 20,`
  line
  line `he shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34268)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34268&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, and subject to the condition of previous publication, by notification, make rules to carry out`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which education may be regulated by the Administrator in Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions which every existing school shall be required to comply;`
  line
  line `(c) establishment of a new school or the opening of a higher class or the closing down of an`
  line `existing class in an existing school;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner in which an application for recognition of a school shall be made;`
  line
  line `(e) the facilities to be provided by a school to obtain recognition;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which, and the authority to which, an appeal against the refusal or withdrawal of`
  line `recognition shall be made;`
  line
  line `(g) the minimum qualifications for, and method of recruitment, and the terms and conditions of`
  line `service of employees;`
  line
  line `(h) the authorities to be specified for the purposes of the different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) the particulars which a scheme of management shall contain, and the manner in which such`
  line `scheme shall be made;`
  line
  line `(j) variations and modifications which may be made in the scheme of management for a`
  line `recognised school which does not receive any aid;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions under which aid may be granted to recognised schools, and on the violation of`
  line `which aid may be stopped, reduced or suspended;`
  line
  line `(l) the part of the expenditure of a recognised school which is to be covered by aid;`
  line
  line `(m) particulars of school property which should be furnished to the appropriate authority;`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which, and the time within which, an appeal shall be preferred to the`
  line `Administrator against an order made in relation to the transfer, mortgage or lien of any school`
  line property;
  line
  line `(o) the Code of Conduct for the employees and the disciplinary action to be taken for the`
  line `violation thereof;`
  line
  line `(p) the benefits which should be granted to the employees of recognised private schools;`
  line
  line `(q) admissions to a recognised school;`
  line
  line `(r) fees and other charges which may be collected by an aided school;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of inspection of recognised schools;`
  line
  line `(t) the term of office, travelling and other allowances payable to the members of the Advisory`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(u) financial and other returns to be filed by the managing committee of recognised private`
  line `schools, and the authority by which such returns shall be audited;`
  line
  line `(v) educational purposes for which the income derived by way of fees by recognised unaided`
  line `schools shall be spent;`
  line
  line `(w) manner of accounting and operation of school funds and other funds of a recognised private`
  line school;
  line
  line `(x) fees, not exceeding one rupee, for preferring any appeal under this Act;`
  line
  line `(y) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annualment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34269)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397&sectionId=34269&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00001_197318_1517807317397
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
